        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 7:56PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 756 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Hugo to 6 miles east of Boyero, or
extending from 12 miles southeast of Limon to 25 miles south of
Flagler, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hugo and Boyero.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
